  "argument": "The e-cigarette Prohibition Act refers to the legislation enacted around May 2019 that bans the production, manufacture, import, export, transport, sale, distribution, storage, and advertisement of e-cigarettes (vapes) in India. This ban was instituted following the Indian Council of Medical Research's (ICMR) White Paper dated 29th May, 2019, which addressed the health concerns associated with electronic nicotine delivery systems. The Act is referenced in various legal documents concerning the prohibition of e-cigarettes in India. Although the specific text of the Act is not provided in the retrieved evidence, it clearly established the legal framework for prohibition of e-cigarettes starting May 2019.",
  "conclusion": "The e-cigarette Prohibition Act is the Indian law enacted around May 2019 that bans the manufacturing, sale, and use of e-cigarettes (vapes) in India following health concerns raised by the ICMR, thus legally prohibiting e-cigarettes nationwide."
}

