  "argument": "The e-cigarette Prohibition Act enacted around May 2019 bans the production, manufacture, import, export, transport, sale, distribution, storage, and advertisement of e-cigarettes (vapes) in India. Owning a vape device falls under this prohibition as it relates to possession of e-cigarettes, which are illegal under the Act. Although the retrieved evidence does not specify exact penalties, owning a vape likely subjects the person to legal consequences under this ban, including possible confiscation or penalties as per the law prohibiting electronic nicotine delivery systems.",
